# SettleFlow Core Rules

Read the relevant plan before writing code:
- Backend: `docs/backend-plan.md`
- Frontend: `docs/frontend-plan.md`

## Non-Negotiable

- Never change architecture unless explicitly approved
- Never rename folders
- Never replace libraries
- Never rewrite existing code unless fixing a bug
- Always extend the current architecture
- If unsure, ask instead of assuming

## Milestone Workflow

- Build **one milestone at a time** (B0–B8 backend, then F0–F8 frontend)
- Stop after deliverable + tests pass; wait for approval before next milestone
- Exit criteria: write tests → run tests → fix failures → verify deliverable → stop

## Coding Standards

- Max 300 lines/file, 40 lines/function
- No `any`; no commented-out code
- `async/await` only; JSDoc on public functions
